<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Cusset, Adansonia, ser. 2, 17 (3): 298" authorityYear="1978" baseAuthorityName="Baill." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Macropodiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macropodiella heteromorpha" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heteromorpha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Macropodiella heteromorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Vulnerable (
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B42" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010n. Macropodiellaheteromorpha. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185399A8403508. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Macropodiellaheteromorpha. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185399 A 8403508. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 n">Ghogue 2010n</bibRefCitation>
). The taxon is known from four localities, and the area of occupancy is less than 500 km2 and the extent of occurrence estimated at 75 km2. At one of the localities (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Meve’ele">Meve'ele</normalizedToken>
waterfalls) it is proposed to build a hydropower dam. The species is threatened by habitat decline due to future dam construction. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B42" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010n. Macropodiellaheteromorpha. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185399A8403508. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Macropodiellaheteromorpha. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185399 A 8403508. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 n">Ghogue (2010n)</bibRefCitation>
two other localities, Nyong River near Mbalmayo and the Mpoume waterfalls on the Nyong River near Makak, have been listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cusset, C" journalOrPublisher=") Flore du Cameroun" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="51 - 99" refId="B20" refString="Cusset, C, 1987. Podostemaeae - Tristichaceae. In: MESRES (Ed.) Flore du Cameroun 30: 51 - 99" title="Podostemaeae - Tristichaceae. In: MESRES (Ed." volume="30" year="1987">Cusset (1987)</bibRefCitation>
for this species. These two sites have been surveyed by Ghogue but the species has not been seen or collected. 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. heteromorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="heteromorpha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">M. heteromorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, therefore, here reassessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
